<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FF71FD60FD6DFD62" authority="Zilli &amp; Hogenes 2002" authorityName="Zilli &amp; Hogenes" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,656,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="behouneki">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FF71FD60FD6DFD62" bold="true" box="[151,656,690,717]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FF71FD60FE70FD63" bold="true" box="[151,397,690,717]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Eudocima behouneki</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FE73FD60FD6DFD62" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W." box="[405,656,690,717]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="153 - 207" refId="ref41799" refString="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W. (2002) An annotated list of the fruit-piercing moth genus Eudocima Billberg, 1820 (sensu Poole) with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Catocalinae). Quadrifina, 5, 153 - 207." type="journal article" year="2002">Zilli &amp; Hogenes 2002</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFBFFC4FF71FD05FA77FC0B" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FD05FE79FD5F" blockId="19.[151,1437,690,933]" box="[151,388,727,753]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFBFFC4FF79FD05FF05FD5F" box="[159,248,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,198,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-32@66.[201,1387,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 13. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima sikhimensis group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605531/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 13</figureCitation>
: E–F, 21: B)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FD29FA77FC0B" blockId="19.[151,1437,690,933]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FE55FD29FDDBFCBA" box="[435,550,763,788]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mazzeii">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FE55FD29FDDBFCBA" box="[435,550,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mazzeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the black marginal hindwing band is more dentate at the veins (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FAFDFD29FEE6FC97" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="153 - 207" refId="ref41799" refString="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W. (2002) An annotated list of the fruit-piercing moth genus Eudocima Billberg, 1820 (sensu Poole) with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Catocalinae). Quadrifina, 5, 153 - 207." type="journal article" year="2002">Zilli &amp; Hogenes 2002</bibRefCitation>
). This band is also dentate but extends closer to the wing margin in 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FBE9FCCDFB44FC97" box="[1039,1209,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FBE9FCCDFB48FC97" baseAuthorityName="Prout" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[1039,1205,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bathyglypta">E. bathyglypta</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the forewing of that species has greenish flecks, especially proximal to the PM line just above the inner margin. Unlike in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FAD0FC91FF20FC2F" baseAuthorityName="Prout" baseAuthorityYear="1928" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bathyglypta">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FAD0FC91FF20FC2F" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. bathyglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the forewing apex of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FE29FCB5FD9DFC2F" box="[463,608,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="behouneki">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FE29FCB5FD9DFC2F" box="[463,608,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. behouneki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is produced as in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FCC1FCB5FC3BFC2F" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[807,966,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikhimensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FCC1FCB5FC3BFC2F" box="[807,966,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. sikhimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FC1DFCB5FB90FC2E" box="[1019,1133,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mazzeii">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FC1DFCB5FB90FC2E" box="[1019,1133,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mazzeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is endemic to the central southern 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FE9DFC59FE04FC0B" box="[379,505,907,933]" name="Philippines" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Philippines</collectingCountry>
where it replaces 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FD23FC59FCC5FC0A" box="[709,824,907,932]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mazzeii">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FD23FC59FCC5FC0A" box="[709,824,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mazzeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is found to the North (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FB64FC59FA83FC0B" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W." box="[1154,1406,907,933]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="153 - 207" refId="ref41799" refString="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W. (2002) An annotated list of the fruit-piercing moth genus Eudocima Billberg, 1820 (sensu Poole) with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Catocalinae). Quadrifina, 5, 153 - 207." type="journal article" year="2002">Zilli &amp; Hogenes 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
